<h2>The Lifestyle Section</h2>


<p>
Many large newspapers and magazines divide their content into <strong>sections</strong> or categories of news. One reason for doing this is to make it easy for readers to discover the types of articles they want. For example, most publications have a <em>sports</em> section for those wanting to see the recent sports news. On the homepage of most newspapers you can see the sections at the top. On the New York Times homepage, we see “World,” “U.S,” “Politics,” etc. as the sections. 
</p>
