<h3>Example: </h3>


<p>
<strong>Article Title/Headline:</strong> Amid all the noise, here’s how I learned to build a sound oasis
</p>
<p>
<strong>Link to the article: </strong><a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/2022/10/16/amid-all-noise-heres-how-i-learned-build-sound-oasis/">https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/2022/10/16/amid-all-noise-heres-how-i-learned-build-sound-oasis/</a>
</p>
<p>
<strong>Author(s): </strong> Pepita Sándwich
</p>
<p>
<strong>Date published</strong>: October 16, 2022
</p>
<p>
<strong>Summary of the article:</strong>
</p>
<p>
This reporter found living in New York City to be incredibly loud. After a trip to the desert, with very little noise, she began to realize the importance of being intentional about the sounds you hear. She started using specific sounds for specific environments and moods. For example, she would put on rain sounds if she wanted to focus. This has become a process of self-discovery for her. 
</p>
<p>
<strong>Why did you choose this article?</strong>
</p>
<p>
I chose this article because it was told mostly with pictures, which I liked. I also relate to feeling like some cities are too noisy so I wanted to hear Pepita’s ideas. 
</p>
<p>
<strong>Why do you think this was included in the “lifestyle” section of the newspaper?</strong>
</p>
<p>
I think this is part of the “health” definition of lifestyle. It is clear that in our life, we hear sounds all the time. This article talks about how we can control and explore ourselves through the sounds we are constantly exposed to. 
</p>
